<!-- **Direct Answers**
1. `docs-index.json`: yes, that path can change. It is an internal artifact, not a Mintlify contract. But moving it is not “just one script”; it currently fans out through [generate-docs-index.js](/Users/alisonhaire/Documents/Livepeer/Docs-v2-dev/tools/scripts/generate-docs-index.js#L45), workflows, docs, and cleanup scripts.
2. No, not everything in the staged allowlist is actually needed at root.
3. Yes, the real root file `ASSISTANT.md` could move. Mintlify’s current assistant docs expect `.mintlify/Assistant.md` or `.mintlify/ASSISTANT.md`, not a bare root file: [Assistant](https://www.mintlify.com/docs/guides/assistant).
4. Correct: `contribute/` can move. Right now it is wired into routing and tooling via [docs.json](/Users/alisonhaire/Documents/Livepeer/Docs-v2-dev/docs.json#L3065), [docs-index-utils.js](/Users/alisonhaire/Documents/Livepeer/Docs-v2-dev/tools/lib/docs-index-utils.js#L217), and [translate-docs.js](/Users/alisonhaire/Documents/Livepeer/Docs-v2-dev/tools/scripts/i18n/translate-docs.js#L532), so it is a real migration, not an impossible one.
